<text>Potential Energy in Covalent Bond Formation: Reacting Many Chlorine Atoms

Notice that a similar conversion of potential to kinetic/heat energy occurs when any atoms form bonds. The covalent bond between two Cl atoms is similar in strength to a covalent bond between two hydrogen atom, so the amount of potential energy converted to heat energy will also be similar.

 
      

 

 
    </text>
